That could be easily done with some markup as described above. There is no need for any cross browser stuff nor special CSS stuff.

Just a little sample:
qx.Class.define("qx.ui.table.cellrenderer.ReplaceSelectBox",
{
  extend : qx.ui.table.cellrenderer.Replace,

  members :
  {
    // overridden
    _getContentHtml : function(cellInfo) {
      return "<div>" + this.base(arguments, cellInfo) + "<div style='float: right; border-left: 1px solid black;'>X</div></div>";
    }
  }
});

